l landscapes of the United States and Mexico. Drawing on a mix of archival, historical, literary, and legal texts, Saldaña-Portillo shows how los indios/Indians provided the condition of possibility for the emergence of Mexico and the United States.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aIndians, Treatment ofzMexican-American Border RegionxHistory. 0aMestizosxRace identityxHistory. 4aAmerican Studies Association book award winners. 4aJohn Hope Franklin Book Award winner. 4aNational Association for ChicanaChicano Studies Book Award winner. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Hispanic American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374923zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374923423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374923.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles